 BY ANDREW EKEJIUBA The Nigerian Flamingos have qualified for the FIFA U-17 Women’s World Cup, which will be held in India in 2022. The Flamingos were held to a scoreless draw by Ethiopia in the second leg, which was played inside the MKO Abiola Stadium in Abuja at the weekend, to qualify 1-0 on aggregate. After six qualifying matches, the Flamingos have scored 15 goals while conceding none. Africa will be represented by three teams at the FIFA U-17 Women’s World Cup in India in 2022, which will take place from October 11 to October 30. Since its debut in 2008, the FIFA U-17 Women’s World Cup has been contested by the under-17 national teams of FIFA member associations in seven editions. It will be India’s second FIFA competition, following the men’s FIFA U-17 World Cup in 2017, and the first time it will host a FIFA women’s football tournament. 